Troubleshooting Common Issues
Issue 1: Syntax Errors in sudoers File
Problem: visudo reports syntax errors Solution:

# Always use visudo to edit
sudo visudo

# If locked out, boot into recovery mode and fix:
pkexec visudo
# or
sudo -k && sudo visudo
Issue 2: Users Cannot Execute Allowed Commands
Problem: Users get "command not found" or permission denied Solution:

# Check the secure_path setting
sudo visudo
# Ensure secure_path includes necessary directories

# Verify user group membership
groups username
id username
Issue 3: Logging Not Working
Problem: sudo commands are not being logged Solution:

# Check rsyslog is running
sudo systemctl status rsyslog

# Verify log directory permissions
sudo ls -la /var/log/sudo-io/
sudo chmod 750 /var/log/sudo-io/

# Restart logging services
sudo systemctl restart rsyslog
Issue 4: Too Many Authentication Prompts
Problem: Users are prompted for passwords too frequently Solution:

# Adjust timestamp_timeout in sudoers
sudo visudo
# Add or modify: Defaults timestamp_timeout=30
